Implement a shopping cart, including:

* Models
* DTOs
* Repositories
* Services
* Unit tests

API endpoints:

These are the endpoints used by normal users to interact with their shopping cart
POST: /api/my_cart/{product_id}/quantity/{quantity} -> Add a product to the user cart
PUT: /api/my_cart/{product_id}/quantity/{quantity} -> Update a product quantity in the user cart
DELETE: /api/my_cart/{product_id} -> Remove a product from the user cart
GET: /api/my_cart/ -> Get user cart

These endpoints are for admin use:
GET /api/admin/carts -> Get the list of all existing carts

Utilities
* Implement a class AuthUtils with 2 methods:
-- loggedInEmail() -> returns logged in user email or raise an exception otherwise
-- loggedInUsedId() -> returns logged in user id or raise an exception otherwise
-- loggedInUser() -> returns logged in user or raise an exception otherwise

This class will be use by related services to get the logged in user while implementing the cart functionality

Models:

Cart (table = carts)
* A user has only 1 cart (relation must be bidirectional)
* A cart can include 0 or more cart items
* A cart has totalPrice, which is the sum of all item prices

CartItem (table = cart_items)
* A cart item is associated with one product (one-to-many) (bidirectional)
* An item can have a discount and the price of the product
* An item has the quantity of products to be purchased

DTOs:

* CartDTO
* CartItemDTO

Other guidelines:
* Use existing entities as reference for naming conventions and project organization
* Use non primitive types for currency and quantity attributes
